<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap the return from exile of two key 
figures in past dictatorial regimes is threatening the survival of 
haitis caretaker government fueling doubts about whether credible 
elections can be held 
lawlessness plagues this impoverished caribbean nation of 6 
million people violence is on the rise with unpunished political 
killings heightening the sense of fear and distrust 
political leaders say they are under constant death threats and 
never sleep at home fearing assassination 
you drive with your hand on your gun you avoid taking the 
same roads you sleep at friends homes never your own house 
said jeanclaude roy leader of the haitian constitutional union a 
centerleft party 
we will not go into elections with this type of terror in the 
streets said presidential candidate louis dejois jr 
general elections are tentatively planned for nov 4 
critics say president ertha pascaltrouillot is weak breaks 
promises cant control the army and doesnt consult with the 
18member council of state with which she is supposed to govern 
jointly 
many political leaders blame her 4monthold government for 
creating an atmosphere that allowed the return of roger lafontant 
reputed head of the tonton macoutes the brutal militia that 
enforced the 29year duvalier dictatorship 
lafontant was the chief of everybody here it is like the 
return of himmler the head of the gestapo said serge voltaire 
a member of the council of state everybody is afraid of him and 
shes not doing anything 
the duvalier family dictatorship which began in 1957 when 
francois duvalier gained the presidency ended in 1986 when his son 
jeanclaude baby doc duvalier fled the country after months of 
civil disorder 
also back from exile is retired army maj gen williams regala 
who went to the united states following the march ouster of lt 
gen prosper avril one of a succession of military men who ruled 
after jeanclaude duvalier doc fled 
as minister of interior and defense regala was responsible for 
security during the thwarted november 1987 attempt at elections 
balloting was canceled after 34 voters were shot and hacked to 
death by thugs linked to the army 
lafontant who is in hiding has hired three lawyers to aid his 
effort to remain in haiti he said last week before going into 
hiding that he intends to become president 
the pressure has been building for mrs pascaltrouillot to 
arrest lafontant but the army isnt carrying out her orders 
the problem is not madame trouillot the problem is the 
army said social affairs minister claudette werleigh i dont 
know if she has power or even if the general himself has power 
the general is armed forces chief herard abraham who commands a 
corrupt and often violent force of 6000 
its not clear to the army that this democracy is in their 
best interest and because of this they are ambivalent said marc 
bazin former world bank economist and presidential candidate 
but they are not interested in returning to the past 
some haitians speculate that duvalier is to return from his 
french exile 
the duvalierists just want a chance to come back to power 
said ms werleigh and the level of misery is so low in this 
country the people would accept money from duvalierists 
when mrs pascaltrouillot was appointed provisional president 
on march 13 expectations ran high perhaps too high that the 
rampant lawlessness and corruption that was the stamp of 
duvalierism might be stemmed 
how can you expect a transitional government to be expedient 
in bringing justice said bazin you need a government that has 
legitimacy nationally and internationally this will only happen 
with elections 
it is a sentiment shared by the united states which has tied 
renewal of 70 million in aid cut after the election day massacre 
to the holding of legitimate elections 
unfortunately you cant get to democracy without elections 
said us embassy spokeswoman susan clyde only a credibly 
elected government will be able to reform the military and deal 
with financial and lending institutions 
a supreme court judge mrs pascaltrouillot was chosen by a 
coalition of political leaders who organized that mass protests 
that led to avrils ouster 
everyone thought she would be different because she was a 
woman and because the army gave up power to her said ms 
werleigh 
but many political organizations are now clamoring for mrs 
pascaltrouillots resignation and vow to boycott elections if she 
is still in the national palace come november 
the lack of an investigation following the assassination of 
council member serge villard and labor leader jeanmarie montes by 
gunmen wearing army uniforms on june 21 was interpreted by some as 
a clear sign that free and fair elections would be impossible 
we want elections but with security we know danger from the 
past said dr louis roy the main author of the 1987 
constitution and president of the council of state we cant 
continue going backward 
</TEXT>
