<TEXT>
this just in us army of imperialist aggression 
continues to support the traitor roh taewoo and his puppet south 
korean government of satanic hooligans 
flashback to the cold war 
no just the world according to communist north koreas official 
news agency where strident near hysterical namecalling of 
longtime enemies remains daily fare and helps keep tension high on 
the korean peninsula 
in the era of glasnost in the soviet union and a crumbling 
socialist world reports from north koreas central news agency 
seem an anachronism final dispatches from the cold war front 
some examples of recent articles from the news agency often 
quoting other north korean media monitored in tokyo 
the official korean roman catholics association was quoted as 
calling seouls arrest of south koreans who traveled to the north a 
human strangulation which can be committed only by satanic 
hooligans without an iota of human reason and national conscience 
the united states which fought with the south against the 
north 40 years ago is the midwife and wirepuller of the dlp the 
governing party in seoul 
gis stationed in south korea are soldiers of the us 
imperialist aggression army 
president roh taewoo of south korea is usually referred to as 
a traitor he is forever up to something sinister 
among the names given his followers are group of heinous 
stranglers of democracy or simply gangsters they pass 
legislation further fascistizing the south korean sociopolitical 
life or they try with bloodshot eyes to obliterate democratic 
forces in the south 
the north korean media were a bit more gracious after roh 
announced last week a proposal to open the border between the rival 
nations he was called the south korean chief executive in 
reports on his proposal but a few days later he was a traitor 
again 
in comparison with the north korean media the few other 
remaining hardline communist nations tend to use language not 
quite so vitriolic 
vietnams media for example are using the once standard us 
imperialists less frequently as hanoi seeks to improve relations 
with washington 
neutral terms such as the government in washington appear as 
frequently as yankee aggression in the official cuban news 
agency prensa latina 
and in communist china staterun media forgo the use of nasty 
adjectives on reports about the rival nationalist chinese 
government on taiwan 
hajime izumi an associate professor at the university of 
shizuoka said he doubts glasnost will reach north korea known 
as one of the most isolated countries in the world any time soon 
a specialist in north korean affairs izumi says the tightly 
controlled pyongyang media prevent the average citizen from knowing 
much about the outside world particularly the more affluent south 
if such information were to become widely available izumi said 
criticism toward the leadership in north korea would increase 
izumi who visited pyongyang twice last year said the strident 
news reports were primarily for domestic consumption 
he said north korean officials told him not to pay much 
attention to the cold war terminology because its main purpose is 
to indoctrinate the countrys own citizens 
but not all is antiamerican antiroh venom on the north korean 
wire 
