<TEXT>
a psychiatrist testifying in behalf of the 
rock band judas priest said two men who allegedly shot themselves 
because of subliminal messages by the group had a number of risk 
factors that could lead to suicide 
donald lunde who teaches at stanford university testified 
monday the two men exhibited personality disorders and suffered 
from drug and alcohol abuse dysfunctional family lives and 
emotional problems 
a combination of these factors can tip the balance toward 
suicide lunde said 
each of these young men were supportive of the notion of 
suicide he said the more of these things you have the 
greater predisposition you have toward suicide 
lunde said his review of extensive medical histories and files 
on both fans of the heavy metal group convinced him the two 
exhibited a combination of risk factors that could potentially lead 
to suicide 
the families of raymond belknap 18 and james vance then 20 
filed suit against the band and cbs records claiming subliminal 
messages on judas priests 1978 stained class album drove the 
young men to a suicide pact 
belknap died from a single blast from a shotgun held to his chin 
on dec 23 1985 vance blew away the lower half of his face but 
survived the shooting he lived three more years and fathered a 
child before dying of complications from his injuries and a 
reaction to medications 
the defense denies subliminal messages exist on the album and 
counters that the young mens troubled lives including family 
violence drug and alcohol abuse poor academics and brushes with 
the law determined their fates not some subconscious command 
lunde who has testified as an expert witness in such 
highprofile cases as the jonestown massacre hillside strangler 
and patty hearst trials said the brain cannot decipher messages 
recorded backward and cannot perceive words masked by music or 
other sound 
you either hear it or you dont we dont have more than one 
mind up there it either hears it it perceives it and it registers 
it or it doesnt he said suicide is not a decision that can 
be made by the subconscious mind 
vivian lynch representing vances family disparaged lundes 
testimony 
i dont think its relevant she said hes not 
knowledgeable in the field of subliminal messages 
the plaintiffs have not finished presenting their case but 
lunde was allowed to testify for the defense monday because it was 
uncertain he would be available when the band and cbs records begin 
to present their cases 
