11channel dfs kopernikus 2 for west germanys deutsche bundespost 
telekom 
the french satellite weighs 4621 pounds and will join a twin 
already in orbit to form a powerful relay system that can serve 400 
million television viewers according to arianespace the 
kopernikus weighs 3126 pounds 
the two satellites are being lifted into space by an ariane 4 
rocket the most recent version introduced in 1988 two years 
behind schedule it features four strapon boosters powered by 
liquid oxygen and liquid hydrogen and stands 190 feet high on the 
launch pad 
different configurations of the strapon boosters using liquid 
or solid fuel can be used according to the needs of individual 
clients 
