severe flooding caused by heavy rainfall in the 
lake baikal region of siberia has killed a number of people and 
left thousands homeless the newspaper sovietskaya rossia said 
today 
more than 400 bridges were swept away as rivers flowing into 
lake baikal overflowed their banks during the rainfall in early 
july the newspaper said power and water supplies in the region 
have been disrupted 
the newspaper said a number of people died in the flooding but 
did not give a death toll 
in the city of chita 2500 miles east of moscow residents 
ignored warnings by officials to take precautions against the 
predicted rainstorms 
several days before the flood we had arranged for a special 
car with a loudspeaker to mve along the streets of the city warning 
people about the danger said chita mayor yuri timofeev but 
people only laughed at us 
according to sovietskaya rossia the flooding caused 635 
million in damages including 270 million in farm damage more 
than 600 cattle and 10000 sheep drowned in the flooding the 
report said 
the newspaper said a regional task force has been set up to deal 
with the emergency 
sovietskaya rossia said meteorologists were predicting more rain 
in august 
the newspaper blamed much of the damage on the intentional 
destruction of forests in the region the situation is aggravated 
by the fact that thoughtless largescale woodfelling renders the 
region particularly vulnerable to any summer rains it said 
