<TEXT>
a 3yearold girl received a transplanted 
liver and small intestine today in a rare operation that lasted 
nearly 14 hours 
tracey kay gonzales of corpus christi texas was in critical 
condition and breathing with the help of a respirator in the 
intensive care unit at childrens hospital following the surgery 
said hospital spokeswoman sue cardillo the operation began at 525 
pm monday and ended about 710 am today 
everybody seems to feel it went fairly well ms cardillo 
said it will be at least a week before doctors are able to form 
any type of prognosis if then 
ms cardillo said the next three days will be especially 
critical and doctors will watch closely to see if the organs are 
functioning properly and free of infection 
tracey needed the double transplant because of a condition 
called short gut syndrome ms cardillo said her liver was damaged 
by a highprotein liquid she was fed intravenously since birth 
a child with short gut syndrome has no way to absorb 
nutrition ms cardillo said there isnt enough intestine 
there to do any good her skin is very yellow from the liver 
damage 
small intestine transplants have a poor success rate since 
1983 three adults and three children have died within a year of 
their surgeries at pittsburgh hospitals 
tracey has been a patient at childrens hospital since april 22 
ms cardillo said the donor of her new organs was not identified 
the girls large intestine or colon functions normally 
an estimated 2000 children are born with short gut syndrome in 
the united states every year 
dr john fung announced earlier this year what he called the 
worlds first successful small intestine transplant on a man who 
was shot in the abdomen 
the man who was not identified was able to eat after the april 
operation but still was recovering fung told the university of 
pittsburghs board of trustees 
threeyearold tabatha foster of madisonville ky died 192 
days after a 1987 transplant of parts of her stomach and colon and 
her pancreas liver and small intestine 
rolandrea rolly dodge another 3yearold girl from 
fruitland nm died three months after her november 1988 
transplant of part of her colon and her stomach pancreas liver 
and small intestine 
an unidentified 6yearold girl died hours after a transplanted 
small intestine replaced an organ damaged in a 1983 swimmingpool 
accident 
