at 230 pm edt arthurs top sustained winds of 40 mph just 
1 mph above the speed required for namedstorm status were 
centered near latitude 107 north and longitude 585 west or about 
160 miles east of trinidad it was moving west at about 20 mph and 
was expected to continue that motion through the day said hal 
gerrish of the national hurricane center 
