engineers and photographers from the united 
states japan west germany and britain have begun a 
hightechnology investigation into what causes the mysterious 
circles that appear suddenly among crops in england and elsewhere 
in europe 
equipped with 18 million worth of heatseeking cameras and 
other sophisticated gear they will be watching fields in the 
southwest county of wiltshire for the next three weeks 
they will try to capture on film whatever it is that flattens 
crops in decorative patters of perfectly formed circles some with 
concentric rings and other shapes 
the circles have been variously attributed to whirlwinds 
witches magnetic forces animals hoaxers and spaceships 
team members are using light and sound equipment to try to 
locate the source in the vale of pewsey a hilly district dividing 
wiltshire between salisbury plain and the marlborough downs 75 
miles southwest of london 
the circles were recorded in england as far back as 1678 but 
circles which appeared in a vale of pewsey wheat field last week 
were more elaborate than usual the circles were linked and some 
had flattened straight areas like arms projecting from them 
in other countries circles have been reported in sand snow and 
rice paddies 
colin andrews coordinator of the watch which began on monday 
said this is a determined effort to secure on highquality film 
the full event whatever that event will ultimately turn out to 
be 
amateur photographers who spent a night in the area last year 
saw nothing but in the morning they found circles in a field 
behind them 
