<TEXT>
a federal judge stopped the justice 
departments antipornography unit from prosecuting a mailorder 
distributor of sexuallyoriented magazines and videos in more than 
one jurisdiction 
us district judge joyce hens green issued the preliminary 
injunction on monday after finding evidence to suggest that federal 
prosecutors had investigated phe inc with the intention of 
forcing the north carolina company also known as adam and eve 
out of business 
the allegations by the company and its owner philip d harvey 
suggest a concerted effort through harassment and threats of 
multiple prosecution to suppress plaintiffs constitutionally 
protected activities the judge said 
she issued a preliminary injunction barring the justice 
department from bringing charges in more than one federal 
jurisdiction at one time 
bruce ennis who represented the company said the justice 
departments national obscenity enforcement unit has pursued a 
strategy of trying to wear down the financial resources of sexually 
oriented businesses by threatening to bring a series of indictments 
in numerous jurisdictions 
he said greens ruling casts a real cloud over the national 
obscenity enforcement units new tactic of threatening multiple 
indictments as a way of coercing adult materials distributors to go 
out of business 
ennis presented evidence that the justice department used 
similar tactics to force pak ventures another distributor of adult 
magazines and videos to go out of business 
in her ruling green noted that it is not without significance 
that defendants have not contested disputed or refuted any of the 
factual assertions contained in the declarations presented by 
plaintiffs 
taken as a whole these allegations suggest a concerted effort 
by the defendants through harassment and threats of multiple 
prosecutions to suppress plaintiffs constitutionally protected 
activities 
intrusive and intimidating searches of the companys 
carrboro nc offices and the admitted desire to get harvey 
out of business substantiate plaintiffs allegations of bad 
faith green ruled 
federal prosecutors in utah and the western district of kentucky 
had threatened to bring charges against adam and eve 
earlier threats were made in the eastern district of north 
carolina even though the fbi had advised prosecutors that the 
materials distributed by phe were not obscene by bureau standards 
according to the ruling 
in 1988 another federal judge issued a similar injunction to 
bar multiple prosecutions of avram freedberg and his stamford 
conn company freedberg ultimately entered a guilty plea agreed 
to get out of the mailorder business and dropped his lawsuit 
