a story of sexual abuse prostitution and 
judicial bribery told to a legislative committee investigating an 
omaha credit union failure was a carefully crafted hoax a 
grand jury said tuesday 
in a 42page report the douglas county grand jury debunked many 
of the rumors that have surrounded the 1988 failure of the franklin 
community federal credit union 
besides its report the grand jury also issued three 
indictments two of them charging perjury against witnesses who 
claimed to the legislature that they were victims 
a federal grand jury also is investigating franklinrelated 
matters the county grand jury said it decided that financial 
matters including a fund shortage of about 39 million were best 
left to the federal grand jury 
perhaps never in the history of douglas county has the 
discordant multitude played so feverishly upon the rumor pipe as in 
the allegations of sexual misconduct surrounding franklin the 
grand jury report said 
in the wake of the franklin collapse allegations and rumors 
arose of sexual abuse of children of an adult male homosexual 
prostitution ring of drug use and cult activities some involving 
prominent citizens 
the grand jury cited many prominent residents by name and 
cleared them of wrongdoing its report indicated that the names may 
have been raised in rumors because of their prominence 
the grand jury said it found no credible evidence of child 
sexual abuse interstate transportation of minors drug trafficking 
or participation in a pornography ring by former franklin manager 
lawrence e king jr or other franklin officials and employees 
king a prominent businessman who sang the national anthem at 
the 1984 republican national convention still faces 40 counts in 
federal court of conspiracy fraud and federal income tax evasion 
he is accused of diverting money for personal use he was ruled 
incompetent to stand trial and is receiving psychiatric treatment 
those indicted by the grand jury included alisha j owen and 
paul a bonacci who had claimed they were victims and gave 
videotaped statements to the special legislative committee 
investigating franklinrelated matters 
there is no doubt after reviewing all relevant evidence that 
the story of sexual abuse drugs prostitution and judicial 
bribery presented in the legislative videotapes is a carefully 
crafted hoax scripted by a person or persons with considerable 
knowledge of the people and institutions of omaha the grand jury 
report said 
ms owen 21 of omaha was charged with eight counts of perjury 
and bonacci 22 also of omaha was indicted on three counts of 
perjury 
the grand jury also handed up an indictment charging two counts 
of pandering against alan a baer 67 an omaha businessman who 
once owned an omahabased department store chain 
the indictment accused baer of giving something of value to two 
males to become a prostitute or commit an act of prostitution but 
the grand jury reported it didnt find any connection between baer 
and the credit union 
its report said many of the allegations made against baer were 
false and it appears baer was written into the script because of 
his wealth 
baers office referred calls to his attorney steve seline who 
stressed that baer was cleared of any sexual exploitation of 
minors seline said the pandering charges against baer which 
involved adults were incorrect and inappropriate 
ms owen is serving time in the nebraska center for women in 
york for writing bad checks she was declining all interviews said 
lawrence wayne superintendent of the womens prison 
her attorney henry c rosenthal jr was out of town and 
unavailable for comment tuesday his omaha office said 
bonacci is serving time in the lincoln correctional center for 
sexually assaulting a boy and could not be reached for comment 
tuesday 
the grand jury reported it hadnt found any evidence to support 
allegations against former omaha worldherald publisher harold 
andersen in march andersen acknowledged he had been named in the 
rumors and said he had done nothing improper 
the grand jury found no evidence to support allegations that 
harold andersen was involved in sexual misconduct of other illegal 
activity said the grand jury report 
andersens only connection with franklin was as cochair of the 
fundraising committee for a new credit union building the motive 
for naming him was probably politically generated due to his 
position as publisher of the omaha worldherald at that time it 
said 
