guard failed to adequately monitor the exxon valdez via radar 
hazelwood was acquitted at his twomonth trial of being drunk 
and reckless but was convicted of one misdemeanor charge of 
negligent discharge of oil he was ordered to pay 50000 
restitution and spend 1000 hours cleaning beaches at prince 
william sound he is appealing the verdict 
an administrative hearing resembles a trial but is held without 
a jury before an administrative law judge the hearing could last 
anywhere from a day to weeks 
