solidarity reported similar incidents but called these mistakes 
rather than deliberate attempts to cheat 
the us observer team said it would make its comments to 
election officials 
mongolia is especially eager that the election be perceived as 
fair because secretary of state james a baker iii is to visit next 
week and discuss extending mostfavored nation trade status to 
mongolia 
formed only over the past few months the five noncommunist 
parties claim a combined membership of about 12000 to the ruling 
partys 98000 
although the opposition appears to have substantial support in 
cities where half of mongolias 2 million people live it has had 
to scramble to reach the rural people 
many herders are only dimly aware of the mass demonstrations in 
ulan bator beginning in december that forced the communists to 
agree to elections they know even less of the anticommunist 
revolutions in eastern europe that inspired mongolias opposition 
the opposition hopes however to win a significant presence in 
the 53seat small hural which will govern between the great 
hurals annual sessions 
in the great hural one seat is allocated for every 2000 rural 
residents but only every 10000 urban residents hurting the 
citybased opposition 
the communists recently have embraced many of the goals of the 
opposition including its demand for marketstyle economic reforms 
