<TEXT>
an ariane rocket successfully 
lifted a double payload of french and german tv satellites into 
orbit tuesday night five months after a similar rocket exploded 
minutes after takeoff 
the rocket blasted off at 725 pm 625 pm edt from the 
ariane space center in french guiana on the northeast coast of 
south america and deployed the two satellites into orbit in less 
than 25 minutes officials reported 
ariane flight 37 was the first launch of a european rocket since 
an ariane carrying two japanese communications satellites blew up 
less than two minutes after takeoff feb 22 launches were 
suspended after the accident 
tuesdays flight put the fivechannel french television 
satellite tdf 2 and the 11channel dfs kopernikus 2 for west 
germanys deutsche bundespost telekom into geostationary orbit 
always staying above the same spot on the earths surface 
all preparations proceeded smoothly mission chief yvan cherica 
reported he said the weather was good despite worries of a storm 
before the launch 
the ariane project has been dogged by embarrassing and costly 
setbacks including rockets that have exploded or crashed and 
expensive delays 
but ariane rockets dominate the private aerospace industry 
carrying about half the worlds commercial payloads into space 
arianespace the commercial branch of the european space agency 
has contracts worth 28 billion to launch 37 more satellites 
the french satellite launched tuesday weighs 4621 pounds and 
will join a twin already in orbit to form a powerful relay system 
that can serve 400 million television viewers arianespace said 
kopernikus weighs 3126 pounds 
tuesdays flight is important in two ways said arianespace 
directorgeneral charles bigot 
it is putting into orbit two satellites of the countries who 
have given the most support to ariane politically technologically 
and industrially it is also the flight in which we pick up after 
the failure of flight 36 
ariane officials say that failure was caused by a small piece of 
cloth that clogged a line carrying water coolant to one engine 
the french weekly lexpress said sabotage may have caused that 
explosion and at least two previous ariane failures 
arianespace officials have said no evidence of sabotage emerged 
but technical and security checks would be intensified 
februarys failure was the fifth in the ariane series and was 
particularly costly because arianespace had lobbied hard for the 
japanese contracts 
tuesdays satellites were lifted into space by an ariane 4 
rocket the latest version introduced in 1988 it features four 
strapon boosters powered by liquid oxygen and liquid hydrogen and 
stands 190 feet high on the launch pad 
a newer version the heavylift launcher ariane 5 is being 
developed for planned introduction in 1995 
arianespace is a consortium made up of aerospace electronics 
and banking companies from 11 western european countries belgium 
britain denmark france ireland italy netherlands spain 
switzerland sweden and west germany 
its rockets have sent into space 45 commercial satellites from 
canada france west germany britain india italy spain and the 
united states as well as international organizations such as 
intelsat and eutelsat 
ariane is facing increased competition however from american 
privatesector rockets including the titan4 made by martin 
marietta corp general dynamics atlascentaur and the delta built 
by mcdonnell douglas 
other rivals include chinas long march rocket the soviet 
unions proton and japans h2 rocket now under development 
until now us rockets have mainly launched military and 
scientific satellites under the supervision of the us air force 
and the national aeronautics and space administration 
</TEXT>
