injunction to continue freezing accounts the sec has identified as 
holding the illegally obtained profits in the contelgte case us 
district judge charles haight jr granted the injunction 
kidney said nine swiss bank employees bought contel securities 
in the days that preceded disclosure of a 6 billion merger of the 
company and gte they were the latest to be mentioned in the probe 
the sec alleged in court papers filed july 13 the day after the 
contelgte merger was announced that individuals or entities 
whose identities are yet unknown used inside information about 
the deal to make profits of at least 1 million 
on friday the sec named four west germans and three european 
entities that allegedly traded contel securities based on inside 
information about the thenundisclosed buyout 
one of the germans has told investigators he overheard a 
conversation about the pending merger at a restaurant kidney said 
kidney said other individuals or companies that ordered the 
purchase of large blocks of contel securities through european bank 
accounts have not yet come forward 
he said it could take months before they were identified because 
the us government would have to use international treaties to 
force the banks in switzerland west germany and luxembourg to 
identify their customers 
he said union bank of switzerland was cooperating in the 
investigation and had interviewed six of its nine employees who 
bought contel call options on july 10 and 11 for their own accounts 
a call option is the right to buy 100 shares of a stock or stock 
index at a set price before a certain date because contel stock 
jumped in price after the buyout proposal was revealed a buyer of 
its call options at the preannouncement price could reap big 
profits after disclosure of the deal 
the six union bank employees were identified as frederic 
galliard alfred keller rolf koechli phillip colliard thierry 
racine and oliver roth 
bank attorney john dickey said the employees most of whom 
worked in the banks trading department in geneva bought the 
securities because they noticed an increase in contel call option 
trading and because a substantial customer had placed a large 
order for contel securities 
the customer was not identified 
the three other union bank employees had not been interviewed 
because two were on vacation and one was recovering from injuries 
from an automobile accident dickey said 
the west germans named friday by the sec are ortwin heider of 
hofheim hansjurgen klisch and hannelore mirbachkrahn both of 
meerbusch and bodo pawlik of ratingen 
the sec complaint also identified three entities accused of 
violating insider trading laws union investment a dusseldorf 
mutual fund and two companies with offices in switzerland nalasag 
corp in geneva and sigesse sa in lausanne 
