reuters holdings plc the british news agency and 
financial information services group said tuesday that earnings 
jumped 27 percent in the first half of the year helped by strong 
sales in all major markets particularly europe 
reuters said earnings for the six months ended june 30 totaled 
108 million pounds or 188 million compared with 853 million 
pounds or 148 million in the same period a year ago 
sales gained 26 percent to 6883 million pounds or 12 billion 
from 5483 million pounds 954 million 
the company said sales strength was partly due to the relative 
weakness of the pound during the period that makes british 
companies more competitive in selling products and services in 
other countries 
the pound has since moved up to 18month highs against the 
dollar and ninemonth highs against the german mark on tuesday 
the pound was quoted at 182 
reuters noted in its statement that conditions in financial 
markets remain difficult and cancellations of reuter services 
which were already high have recently risen further 
the company didnt break out quarterly results it isnt 
required to under british law 
the figures were converted at the companyprovided exchange rate 
of 174 to the pound 
