<TEXT>
pepsico inc said tuesday its earnings for the 
second quarter rose 10 percent from a year ago on a 17 percent 
sales gain led by doubledigit advances in the snack food and 
restaurant divisions 
the company whose largest business is soft drinks said it 
earned 2925 million or 110 a share in the three months ended 
june 16 compared with 2649 million or 1 a share a year earlier 
revenue for the quarter rose to 420 billion from 359 billion 
a year earlier 
the latest results were reduced by a 55 million aftertax 
charge resulting from a customer bankruptcy while the 1989 results 
were boosted by 222 million mainly resulting from the companys 
decision to keep rather than sell a bottling operation in japan 
softdrink sales rose 8 percent to 16 billion but operating 
profit fell 3 percent to 2332 million 
if onetime items are excluded from both years operating profit 
from soft drinks would have been up 15 percent 
domestic soft drink sales rose 5 percent including a 4 percent 
gain in bottler case sales that were driven by doubledigit growth 
in the diet pepesi products strong gains in mountain dew and a 
solid pepsi brand performance 
international soft drink sales rose 23 percent 
snack foods sales climbed 24 percent to 12 billion including 
sales from smiths and walkers acquired last year while operating 
profit rose 18 percent to 2262 million 
excluding smiths and walkers and onetime items in both years 
sales and operating profit would have each risen 12 percent 
domestic sales rose 6 percent while international sales more 
than doubled helped by a strong volume increases and lower 
commodity costs its brands include cheetos santitas and crunch 
tators 
restaurant sales rose 22 percent to 14 billion while operating 
profit rose 36 percent to 2286 million excluding the impact od 
onetime items operating profit would risen 25 percent 
sales rose 25 percent to 676 million at the pizza hut chain 21 
percent to 399 million at taco bell and 18 percent to 358 million 
at kentucky fried chicken 
for the first half pepsico said it earned 4744 million or 
178 a share up 102 percent from 4300 million or 162 a 
share a year ago 
revenue for the first half rose 20 percent to 788 billion from 
655 billion a year earlier 
