showed only 28 percent of the corn crop at the silking stage as of 
sunday compared with the average of 62 percent for that date 
the usda said 36 percent of the soybean crop was blooming 
compared with a 57 percent norm and 6 percent of soybeans were 
setting pods compared with the average of 20 percent 
lespinasse said fears are filtering into the market that an 
early frost could damage latematuring crops reducing the overall 
yields 
